  "title": "Migration page UX: fix empty page on refresh, polling, reset button with confirmation dialog",
  "description": "Fixes and enhancements to `frontend/pages/admin/migration.vue`. All four issues must be resolved.\n\n## ANALYSIS FINDINGS (pre-read by orchestrator)\nThe current migration.vue:\n- Uses `useApi<MigrationStatus>` in `fetchStatus()` — this is a Nuxt composable, calling it inside a plain async function (not inside `setup()` or `useAsyncData`) can cause issues on hard refresh / SSR hydration\n- `onMounted(() => { fetchStatus() })` — onMounted is correct but `useApi` (likely wraps `useFetch`/`useAsyncData`) must not be called outside setup context\n- Polling is implemented via raw `setInterval` stored in `ref<NodeJS.Timeout | null>` — functional but has a bug: `fetchStatus()` calls `useApi()` which is a composable and cannot be called in a callback context\n- No reset button exists\n- Page has `layout: false` and uses `NuxtLayout name=\"admin\"` directly\n\n## Fix 1 — Fix empty page on hard refresh (SSR/hydration bug)\nRoot cause: `useApi` is a Nuxt composable that internally calls `useFetch`/`useAsyncData`. These CANNOT be called inside `onMounted`, intervals, or event handlers — they must be called at setup-time.\n\nSolution: Replace `useApi` inside `fetchStatus` with a raw `$fetch` call (or `useApiFetch` which is already imported as a composable returning a fetch function).\n\nRewrite the data fetching pattern:\n```typescript\n// At setup time (top level of <script setup>):\nconst { $apiFetch } = useNuxtApp()  // or use useApiFetch() composable that returns fetch fn\n// OR simply:\nconst apiFetch = useApiFetch()  // already exists in the component\n\n// fetchStatus should use apiFetch (not useApi):\nconst fetchStatus = async () => {\n  isLoading.value = true\n  try {\n    const data = await apiFetch<MigrationStatus>('/admin/migration/status')\n    status.value = data\n    if (status.value?.overall_status === 'RUNNING') {\n      startPolling()\n    } else {\n      stopPolling()\n    }\n  } catch (err: any) {\n    addToast({ type: 'error', title: 'Ошибка статуса', message: err.message })\n  } finally {\n    isLoading.value = false\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCheck how `useApiFetch` composable is implemented — if it returns a function (like `$fetch` wrapper), use it directly in fetchStatus. If `useApi` is a different composable, look at `composables/useApi.ts` or `composables/useApiFetch.ts` first.\n\nAlso ensure `fetchStatus()` is called in `onMounted` (already exists). Add `{ server: false }` if needed to avoid SSR execution.\n\n## Fix 2 — Fix polling: use setInterval correctly\nThe current polling calls `fetchStatus()` inside `setInterval` callback. Since `fetchStatus` now uses `apiFetch` (not a composable), this is fine. Verify the existing polling logic works:\n```typescript\nconst startPolling = () => {\n  if (refreshInterval.value) return\n  refreshInterval.value = setInterval(fetchStatus, 3000)\n}\n\nconst stopPolling = () => {\n  if (refreshInterval.value) {\n    clearInterval(refreshInterval.value)\n    refreshInterval.value = null\n  }\n}\n```\nEnsure polling starts when status is RUNNING and stops in onUnmounted.\n\n## Fix 3 — Add reset button with confirmation dialog\nAdd a new `resetMigration` function:\n```typescript\nconst showResetConfirm = ref(false)\nconst isResetting = ref(false)\n\nconst confirmReset = () => {\n  showResetConfirm.value = true\n}\n\nconst resetMigration = async () => {\n  showResetConfirm.value = false\n  isResetting.value = true\n  try {\n    await apiFetch('/admin/migration/reset', { method: 'DELETE' })\n    addToast({ type: 'success', title: 'Данные миграции очищены' })\n    status.value = null\n    isLoading.value = true\n    await fetchStatus()\n  } catch (err: any) {\n    addToast({ type: 'error', title: 'Ошибка очистки', message: err.message })\n  } finally {\n    isResetting.value = false\n  }\n}\n```\n\nIn the template, add reset button in `#header-actions` slot (after all other buttons):\n```html\n<UButton\n  variant=\"danger\"\n  @click=\"confirmReset\"\n  :loading=\"isResetting\"\n  :disabled=\"isActionPending\"\n  data-testid=\"migration-reset-btn\"\n>\n  <template #icon><Icon name=\"ph:trash-bold\" /></template>\n  Очистить данные\n</UButton>\n```\n\nAdd confirmation dialog (modal) in the template. Use existing UModal or UDialog component if available, otherwise build inline with a `<Teleport to=\"body\">` overlay:\n```html\n<Teleport to=\"body\">\n  <div v-if=\"showResetConfirm\" class=\"confirm-overlay\" role=\"dialog\" aria-modal=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"reset-dialog-title\">\n    <div class=\"confirm-dialog\">\n      <h3 id=\"reset-dialog-title\">Подтверждение очистки</h3>\n      <p>Это действие удалит ВСЕ товары, категории, заказы и блог-посты, созданные миграцией. Действие необратимо.</p>\n      <div class=\"confirm-actions\">\n        <UButton variant=\"secondary\" @click=\"showResetConfirm = false\" data-testid=\"migration-reset-cancel-btn\">Отмена</UButton>\n        <UButton variant=\"danger\" @click=\"resetMigration\" data-testid=\"migration-reset-confirm-btn\">Да, удалить всё</UButton>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</Teleport>\n```\nAdd CSS for `.confirm-overlay` (fixed fullscreen semi-transparent backdrop) and `.confirm-dialog` (centered card, themed, z-index above admin sidebar) using only `var(--color-*)` tokens.\n\n## Fix 4 — Ensure polling resumes correctly after resume action\nAfter `resumeMigration()` calls `fetchStatus()`, if status becomes RUNNING, polling should auto-start. This is already handled by the logic in fetchStatus (if RUNNING → startPolling). Verify it works end-to-end in the template.\n\n## data-testid requirements\nAll interactive elements must have data-testid:\n- `migration-start-btn` (already exists)\n- `migration-pause-btn` (already exists)\n- `migration-resume-btn` (already exists)\n- `migration-reset-btn` (new)\n- `migration-reset-cancel-btn` (new)\n- `migration-reset-confirm-btn` (new)\n- `migration-overall-progress` on the overall progress bar container\n- `migration-entity-card-{key}` on each entity UCard (key = users/categories/products/images/orders)\n\n## Files to check/read before implementing\n1. `frontend/composables/useApiFetch.ts` OR `frontend/composables/useApi.ts` — understand how API calls work\n2. `frontend/components/U/` — check for existing UModal or dialog component\n3. `frontend/assets/css/tokens.css` — use only these tokens for new styles\n\n## Constraints\n- NO useApi() called inside onMounted/setInterval/event handlers — use the imperative fetch function\n- NO inline styles — only var(--color-*) tokens\n- NO new npm packages (use existing VueUse if available, otherwise setInterval is fine)\n- npm install --legacy-peer-deps if any install needed\n- TypeScript strict, no `any` except in catch blocks\n- Confirmation dialog must trap focus (Escape key closes it)\n- data-testid on ALL interactive elements including new ones",
  "depends_on": ["p10_backend_migration_fixes"],
